                                                                                  Day-3
Understand IP addressing and check system IP using ip a or ifconfig.
command: ip a
2: ens33: <BROADCAST,MULTICAST,UP,LOWER_UP> mtu 1500 qdisc fq_codel state UP group default qlen 1000
    link/ether 00:0c:29:b7:aa:92 brd ff:ff:ff:ff:ff:ff
    altname enp2s1
    inet 192.168.8.128/24 brd 192.168.8.255 scope global dynamic noprefixroute ens33
       valid_lft 1512sec preferred_lft 1512sec

Test connectivity using ping to public servers like Google DNS.
command: ping google.com
PING google.com (142.250.67.78) 56(84) bytes of data.
64 bytes from maa05s13-in-f14.1e100.net (142.250.67.78): icmp_seq=1 ttl=128 time=923 ms
64 bytes from maa05s13-in-f14.1e100.net (142.250.67.78): icmp_seq=2 ttl=128 time=410 ms
64 bytes from maa05s13-in-f14.1e100.net (142.250.67.78): icmp_seq=3 ttl=128 time=508 ms
64 bytes from maa05s13-in-f14.1e100.net (142.250.67.78): icmp_seq=4 ttl=128 time=533 ms

Use netstat or ss to inspect open ports and services.
command: netstat -tulnp
Proto Recv-Q Send-Q Local Address           Foreign Address         State       PID/Program name    
tcp        0      0 127.0.0.1:631           0.0.0.0:*               LISTEN      1740/cupsd          
tcp        0      0 127.0.0.54:53           0.0.0.0:*               LISTEN      544/systemd-resolve 
tcp        0      0 0.0.0.0:22              0.0.0.0:*               LISTEN      1/init              
tcp        0      0 127.0.0.53:53           0.0.0.0:*               LISTEN      544/systemd-resolve 
tcp6       0      0 :::3000                 :::*                    LISTEN      1780/grafana        
tcp6       0      0 :::22                   :::*                    LISTEN      1/init              
tcp6       0      0 ::1:631                 :::*                    LISTEN      1740/cupsd          
udp        0      0 0.0.0.0:58326           0.0.0.0:*                           1052/avahi-daemon:  
udp        0      0 0.0.0.0:5353            0.0.0.0:*                           1052/avahi-daemon:  
udp        0      0 127.0.0.54:53           0.0.0.0:*                           544/systemd-resolve 

4.Learn DNS resolution using nslookup and dig.
command: nslookup google.com
  Server:		127.0.0.53
Address:	127.0.0.53#53

Non-authoritative answer:
Name:	google.com
Address: 142.250.67.78
Name:	google.com
Address: 2404:6800:4007:836::200e

5.Trace network path using traceroute.
  command: traceroute google.com
  traceroute to google.com.localdomain (142.251.223.238), 64 hops max
  1   192.168.8.2  0.122ms  0.650ms  0.165ms 
  2   *  *  * 

6.Simulate network failure by disabling interfaces.
  command: ip link set ens33 down
    2: ens33: <BROADCAST,MULTICAST> mtu 1500 qdisc fq_codel state DOWN group default qlen 1000
    link/ether 00:0c:29:b7:aa:92 brd ff:ff:ff:ff:ff:ff
    altname enp2s1
    inet 192.168.8.128/24 brd 192.168.8.255 scope global dynamic noprefixroute ens33
       valid_lft 1434sec preferred_lft 1434sec
ip link set ens33 up
  2: ens33: <BROADCAST,MULTICAST,UP,LOWER_UP> mtu 1500 qdisc fq_codel state UP group default qlen 1000
    link/ether 00:0c:29:b7:aa:92 brd ff:ff:ff:ff:ff:ff
    altname enp2s1

nmcli networking off
ping google.com
ping: google.com: Temporary failure in name resolution

nmcli networking on
ping google.com
PING google.com (142.250.182.142) 56(84) bytes of data.
64 bytes from 142.250.182.142: icmp_seq=1 ttl=128 time=8328 ms

  

